node.text:
I wanted to celebrate three years in business in a proper Josie way 💥 🔥 😂 Thank you for all your amazing support and I’m honoured I get to be apart of your day 🌈 

Hope I made you smile 😃 
Love Sweet Josie 

P.S @livstagrammin and @jocelynmercer11 should this be my meet the teacher video 😂 I feel like it explains everything you need to know about my teaching style 😂 😂

node.text: First voice over video and it was so much harder then I thought it was going to be 😂 But I gave myself a deadline to post one and of course I waited until the last day to get my nerves up to do it 🤗 but I’m happy I finally did one 😃 let me know in the comments if you want another voice over video

node.text:
On my last colour mixing video the question I received most 
“I can get these colours with a small batch but I can’t colour a larger batch without using a ton more. The colours are dull, boring and fade fast, help” 

Simple and most likely answer (although there might be other reasons)  you’re not mixing your colours enough. With the ratios you have to adjust the amount of gel you add to colour a batch 3 times as big BUT it will give you the same exact colour. 
UNLESS you’re under mixing, so why does under mixing give you dull, boring and fading colours ??? 
It’s  because you’re trying to push colour (gels)  particles into a fat (the butter) the food colouring doesn’t want to be mixed with the butter. It’s happy to just stay sitting on top, which is why your colours don’t come out the same. After all it’s easy to mix a small batch by hand but a larger batch is way more difficult 😞  try popping the larger batch you want to colour back into your mixer and mix the colour in on the lowest setting ! 

That way your colours truly start blending together !! Let me know if this was helpful or if you didn’t answer something 🤗 love you ! Happy colouring 🌈

node.text:
Mini transfer cake tutorial 🤗 
Using acetate paper (parchment paper works as well) layer your buttercream ( Swiss, American and Italian all work) onto the acetate sheet, with whatever design you like. I’m using a marble technique 🌈 after laying your buttercream make sure it’s even by running your scraper or offset spatula along the top of it. 

Place your acetate sheet on your room temperature cake 🎂 use your scraper to make sure the layers are touching and there isn’t air trapped between your acetate and cake. 

Place into your freeze for 15-20 minutes or until the sheet comes off clean. Scraper with a warm scraper to get an even smooth surface and then decorate in anyway you want !!!

I finish this cake off with a 1M border and a black ganache drip 🤗 Let me know if you found this helpful below 👇

node.text:
This cake is a disgrace to the sweet Josie Bakes name 😂 that might sound dramatic (and it is…) BUT it had all the potential to be the best striped cake ever!! The colours were on point, the lighting was working for me but NO the stripes were giving me so many issues and I had to change the design and I honestly just hate it 😂 !  So you might be asking yourself,  why post a cake you hate, Josie? Well, It’s a nice reminder that insta is very edited, usually I wouldn’t have posted this cake and quickly scrapped it down and made another ( not ugly ) cake 🎂 but that’s not reality and things don’t always turn out perfect 🤩
Now to kill this cake and move on 😜swipe to see cakes I actually like 😂

I took yesterday’s jade emerald colour and turned it into 4 different colours to make today’s cake 🤩 
with either the addition of white buttercream, a touch of green or some more blue I create a cohesive colour palette 🎨 All from one colour 😊 what do you think of this under water theme cake ?! Let me know below and which colour should I do this next with ?!

node.text:
It’s all about building up your colours! I first start by creating a base color, knowing that I want my end shade to be a emerald Jade colour. I know I’m looking for a rich green with a dominant blue shade popping through 🌈 

Building your colours up also allows you to use less colouring. If I were to just add in blue and green, I would have to use a TON to get this same shade and cancel out any undertone colours. However when I take the time to build up a base colour, then change my tone by adding additional colours on top. I end up using way less  gels and still have a vivid shade 🤗 Let me know if you found this helpful

#colormixing #artreels #artist #cakeartist #cake #art #artistsoninstagram #baking #reels #buttercream #colorful

I’ve definitely cried over macarons 😂 🙈 they can be a pain but once you figure them out and get those feet 🦶 it’s the BEST feeling !!! 
These are Italian macarons, which I haven’t made in forever. I usually use the French method  because it’s faster 💨 and don’t even get my started on the Swiss method 😡 not once have I gotten those to work for me 😂 

Are you tried making macarons and which is your favourite method 🤗 let me know below

node.text:
Bejeweled moon 🌙 first up in my Halloween inspired Bejeweled cakes ⭐️ 
Super in love with this simple style. I used an eggplant purple for the background, a yellowish gold for the accent piping with a # 32 piping tip and finished it off my gold beads (edible don’t worry 😉) 
What else would you like to see in bejeweled cake form 😂

node.text:
Tips on how to create the perfect stripes, tips below 👇 
Also letting the cat out of the bag, I’m planning on filming my first YouTube video on this topic in October 🎉 
A full how to tutorial type of video ( been putting off YouTube forever cause it scares me 😂) anyways ….

⭐️ stripe tips ⭐️ 
Before ANYTHING else make sure your layers are as straight as you can get them! This helps so much when you’re scraping off your stripes. If your cake sides are all uneven, you end up scraping away more buttercream from one area then the other 😑 which is so so hard to fix! 

⭐️ pipe the stripes one at a time instead of icing the whole cake and having to scrape off more then half of the buttercream. In my opinion it creates twice as much work and mess. 

⭐️ let it chill in your freezer for 15 mins or until you can touch the buttercream and it doesn’t come off in your finger. Fill in your colours and start scraping right away, since the cake is chilled you don’t want to let the new buttercream sit to long or it becomes harder to move around the cake 

⭐️ once you are happy with your stripes, run your cake comb under hot water and go around slowly in one motion 🤗 
Let me know below if this help 😘

Yah or naw 🤗
